Charga-Plates]] to imprint account numbers, rather than writing them by hand. *'''1941''', [[Computer]]: [[Konrad Zuse]] develops the first digital computer, the [[Z3 (computer)]] *'''17 November 1947''', [[Transistor]]: [[John Bardeen]], [[Walter Brattain]], and [[William Shockley|Bill Shockley]] at [[AT&T Bell Labs]] made the first transistor. *'''1951''', [[Audio recording]]: Geoff Hill plays back the first [[digital audio]] recording of [[Colonel Bogey's March]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.indiana.edu/~emusic/etext/digital_audio/chapter5_digital.shtml |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128105852/https://www.indiana.edu/~emusic/etext/digital_audio/chapter5_digital.shtml |archive-date=2016-11-28 |title=Digital Audio |work=Introduction to Computer Music}}</ref> *'''1954''', [[digital voltmeter]] replaces analog [[galvanometer]]. *'''1970''', [[Watch]]: [[Pulsar (watch)]] helped [[Hamilton Watch Company]] make real the prototype for the [[digital watch]] that Hamilton Watch Co. designed for the 1968 film ''[[2001: A Space Odyssey (film)|2001: A Space Odyssey]]''. The watch was completed in 1972 and sold for $2,100 USD.[[Watch#Digital]] *'''1973''', [[Telecommunication|Telephone service]]: The first [[VoIP|digital phone message]] was relayed over the [[ARPANET]] system.[https://web.archive.org/web/20090125122045/http://www.utdallas.edu/~bjackson/history.html] *'''December 1975''', [[Still image]]: [[Kodak]] engineer [[Steven Sasson]] creates the first [[digital camera]], weighing eight pounds and saving images to a cassette tape. Exposure time was 23 seconds. [[Digital camera#Early development]] *'''1979''' (?), [[Compact Disc]] *'''1982''', [[Video recording]]: The first [[digital video]] technology was made available.[https://web.archive.org/web/20081229155957/http://www.cytechandprofservices.com/vhistory.htm] *'''March 1, 1997''', [[Player Piano]]: [[QRS]] and [[Baldwin Piano Company|Baldwin]] collaborate to produce the first [[MIDI]]-compatible player piano.[https://web.archive.org/web/20080115221103/http://www.qrsmusic.com/press_details.asp?rid=12] *'''February 13, 1998''', [[Player Violin]]: [[QRS]] patents the first [[MIDI]]-compatible player violin.[http://www.qrsmusic.com/press_details.asp?rid=19] *'''October 1, 1998''', [[Television]]: [[British Sky Broadcasting]] launches the first [[digital television]] network. [[British Sky Broadcasting#Move to Digital]] *'''January 31, 2005''', [[Credit card]]: [[Fujitsu]] patents the Wireless Wallet, a cell phone that doubles as an electronic credit card for more secure transactions.[https://web.archive.org/web/20110612200604/http://www.patentstorm.us/applications/20050187873/fulltext.html]
